1
00:01:22,505 --> 00:01:24,553
Did you lie to me?

2
00:01:25,811 --> 00:01:28,092
I didn't lie...

3
00:01:29,486 --> 00:01:31,733
Then what was it?

4
00:01:35,886 --> 00:01:37,400
I mean...

5
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:42,059
I was trying to find the right moment...

6
00:01:48,828 --> 00:01:50,327
Were you ever going to tell me?

7
00:01:50,327 --> 00:01:51,903
Or were you just going to keep lying?

8
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,473
If I were trying to hide it,
I wouldn't say it now.

9
00:01:54,473 --> 00:01:57,090
So you're saying it was just bad timing?

10
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:58,610
That's not what I mean--

11
00:01:58,610 --> 00:02:00,636
Then what do you mean?

12
00:02:00,636 --> 00:02:02,853
Are you saying you don't have a kid?

13
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:11,716
Did I look that easy to you?

14
00:02:13,331 --> 00:02:15,299
Did you think I was so lonely

15
00:02:15,299 --> 00:02:18,612
that you having a kid wouldn't matter to me?

16
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:21,550
Anything else you want to confess?

17
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:23,190
Any criminal record?

18
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:25,756
I was afraid you'd react like this.

19
00:02:27,482 --> 00:02:29,862
That's why I couldn't tell you.

20
00:02:42,718 --> 00:02:44,784
I was scared.

21
00:02:50,136 --> 00:02:52,223
Because I really liked you...

22
00:03:00,173 --> 00:03:02,473
How do you think that makes me feel?

23
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:04,785
I hate myself for liking you.

24
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:06,638
For trusting someone like you.

25
00:03:06,638 --> 00:03:08,824
I regret it so much.

26
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,153
[Do Hyun]

27
00:03:29,153 --> 00:03:31,654
<i>I'll stop by this weekend to get my things.</i>

28
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:36,933
<i>If it's uncomfortable for you,
I'll come when you're not home.</i>

29
00:04:02,706 --> 00:04:04,932
[Squirtle]

30
00:04:04,932 --> 00:04:06,777
- Hello?
<i>- Where are you?</i>

31
00:04:06,777 --> 00:04:09,270
- At home.
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

32
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:11,563
Having an existential crisis...

33
00:04:11,563 --> 00:04:15,823
Some people create masterpieces at 18,

34
00:04:15,823 --> 00:04:17,310
and some people...

35
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:20,007
are 27 and fixing other people's typos.

36
00:04:20,007 --> 00:04:21,205
I'm coming over.

37
00:04:21,205 --> 00:04:23,128
I just showered and changed...

38
00:04:23,128 --> 00:04:25,774
So what? Just wait for me.

39
00:04:59,213 --> 00:05:01,107
- You know...
- Yeah?

40
00:05:01,107 --> 00:05:03,345
You don't usually try this hard at life.

41
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:06,993
Don't start with me. Just look it over.

42
00:05:06,993 --> 00:05:11,240
Do grad students always write papers this long?

43
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,953
Is it too much?

44
00:05:13,559 --> 00:05:15,165
There's a saying.

45
00:05:15,165 --> 00:05:17,023
"Since I don't have much time,

46
00:05:17,023 --> 00:05:19,516
I'll make this long."

47
00:05:19,516 --> 00:05:21,676
*

48
00:05:21,676 --> 00:05:23,236
See?

49
00:05:23,236 --> 00:05:24,741
The longer it is,

50
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:27,040
the more it shows you're not ready.

51
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,786
So help me tighten it up,

52
00:05:28,786 --> 00:05:31,812
make it sharp and airtight.

53
00:05:32,926 --> 00:05:35,452
Let me benefit from the future great writer.

54
00:05:36,673 --> 00:05:38,306
Nice.

55
00:05:39,515 --> 00:05:41,523
This smells amazing.

56
00:05:41,523 --> 00:05:43,135
This is crazy.

57
00:05:56,591 --> 00:05:57,616
Good, right?

58
00:05:57,616 --> 00:06:00,261
My parents went back to the countryside
for their orchard,

59
00:06:00,261 --> 00:06:02,626
so I basically lived at your place
and ate all your food.

60
00:06:02,626 --> 00:06:05,156
Yeah, I told you to just move in at that point.

61
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:06,702
Right.

62
00:06:16,659 --> 00:06:19,958
Your mom's kimchi fried rice was
seriously the best.

63
00:06:21,752 --> 00:06:23,405
Hey.

64
00:06:24,345 --> 00:06:26,232
What's wrong with you?

65
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,233
I just miss your mom.

66
00:06:35,494 --> 00:06:37,233
Sorry.

67
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,994
Still... it feels nice.

68
00:06:45,009 --> 00:06:47,348
Because I get to talk about my mom.

69
00:06:49,486 --> 00:06:52,059
If I'd known she'd be gone so suddenly,

70
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:55,539
I should have tried harder...

71
00:06:55,539 --> 00:06:58,092
to be a better person.

72
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,125
That's a real shame.

73
00:08:20,063 --> 00:08:23,472
[Listen 25 Convenience Store]

74
00:08:23,472 --> 00:08:25,484
Looks like the power is out.

75
00:08:25,484 --> 00:08:27,005
Do you have cash?

76
00:08:27,005 --> 00:08:29,192
Uh, no...

77
00:08:41,904 --> 00:08:44,083
I don't have cash either.

78
00:08:45,137 --> 00:08:46,394
I'll put this back and go.

79
00:08:46,394 --> 00:08:48,507
No, I'll take care of it.

80
00:08:48,507 --> 00:08:50,660
Why aren't the lights on?

81
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,727
Why's it so dark in here?

82
00:08:54,006 --> 00:08:55,767
Give me a pack of cigarettes.

83
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:58,265
Sorry, the power just went out.

84
00:08:58,265 --> 00:09:00,290
Do you have cash?

85
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,997
Who carries cash these days?

86
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:07,044
The register is down, so cards won't work.

87
00:09:07,044 --> 00:09:09,053
You disrespecting me now?

88
00:09:09,053 --> 00:09:11,044
You looking down on me?

89
00:09:11,044 --> 00:09:12,922
What are you talking about?

90
00:09:12,922 --> 00:09:16,338
She said cards aren't working
because of the blackout.

91
00:09:16,338 --> 00:09:18,579
Who the hell are you?

92
00:09:21,201 --> 00:09:23,640
- Then who the hell are you?
- What?

93
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,329
How dare...

94
00:09:25,329 --> 00:09:26,839
You two...

95
00:09:32,295 --> 00:09:34,614
Give me the cigarettes. Now.

96
00:09:34,614 --> 00:09:35,892
Yes, sir.

97
00:09:35,892 --> 00:09:37,192
What are you staring at, huh?

98
00:09:37,192 --> 00:09:39,525
Police? This is a convenience store
in Yeonhwa-dong.

99
00:09:39,525 --> 00:09:41,561
There's a drunk guy in here...

100
00:09:43,601 --> 00:09:46,500
He's throwing things and threatening us.

101
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,280
Please come right away.

102
00:10:01,969 --> 00:10:05,256
It seems that the whole area is blacked out.

103
00:10:05,256 --> 00:10:08,643
My boss told us to lock up
until the power is back.

104
00:10:08,643 --> 00:10:11,069
I can't even check visitors out anyway.

105
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:13,862
Just in case things get out of hand.

106
00:10:16,634 --> 00:10:18,288
Thank you.

107
00:10:21,420 --> 00:10:23,453
You can lock the door.

108
00:10:39,342 --> 00:10:41,464
Want me to stay with you?

109
00:10:49,829 --> 00:10:52,922
If I go home, it'll be dark there too.

110
00:10:54,042 --> 00:10:55,902
And we don't even have candles.

111
00:11:06,093 --> 00:11:09,560
<i>Those of you who've been with
"Night Walk" for a while know this,</i>

112
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:12,018
<i>I really love cherry blossoms.</i>

113
00:11:12,018 --> 00:11:13,631
You hear this, right?

114
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:18,520
<i>Spring came especially late this year.</i>

115
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:21,453
<i>I've heard the blossoms would bloom late too.</i>

116
00:11:21,453 --> 00:11:23,684
<i>So I waited and waited,</i>

117
00:11:23,684 --> 00:11:26,366
<i>hoping to see them in full bloom...</i>

118
00:11:26,366 --> 00:11:29,826
<i>but then a sudden rain knocked them down early.</i>

119
00:11:30,656 --> 00:11:32,632
<i>In the end, I missed them.</i>

120
00:11:36,609 --> 00:11:40,629
<i>Why do the good things disappear so quickly?</i>

121
00:12:05,506 --> 00:12:07,830
How did he hide having a kid?

122
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:11,569
One turns into two,
and suddenly there are variables.

123
00:12:11,569 --> 00:12:12,930
Oh, no. It's three.

124
00:12:12,930 --> 00:12:15,750
Is this funny to you right now?

125
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:18,216
At least he's not married.

126
00:12:18,216 --> 00:12:20,589
If he's staying at Jun Kyung's place,

127
00:12:20,589 --> 00:12:22,237
it doesn't look like he is raising the kid.

128
00:12:22,237 --> 00:12:24,023
So what's the problem?

129
00:12:24,023 --> 00:12:26,303
He's just divorced, right?

130
00:12:26,303 --> 00:12:28,311
- How old is the kid?
- Stop.

131
00:12:28,311 --> 00:12:29,863
Why does any of that matter now?

132
00:12:29,863 --> 00:12:32,303
Anyway, delete his number.

133
00:12:32,303 --> 00:12:35,216
If you keep it,
you'll just wait for him to call.

134
00:12:35,216 --> 00:12:37,830
And end up calling him when you're lonely.

135
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:39,230
I already deleted it.

136
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:41,416
You probably memorized it.

137
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:44,076
Erase him from your head, too.

138
00:12:46,349 --> 00:12:47,539
You need a drink.

139
00:12:47,539 --> 00:12:49,303
Drink and forget everything.

140
00:12:49,303 --> 00:12:51,131
Let's drink.

141
00:12:53,318 --> 00:12:54,880
Are you really going to break up with him?

142
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,486
Not "going to." We're already done.

143
00:12:56,486 --> 00:12:58,693
Didn't you hear he has a kid?

144
00:12:58,693 --> 00:13:02,633
What better reason is there to break up?

145
00:13:04,808 --> 00:13:06,308
Come on...

146
00:13:06,308 --> 00:13:10,284
It's like you're always waiting for
a reason to leave.

147
00:13:10,284 --> 00:13:11,740
Did you even hear his side?

148
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:13,714
Like... why he couldn't tell you.

149
00:13:15,693 --> 00:13:18,373
Hey, you still love him. Don't you?

150
00:13:18,373 --> 00:13:21,566
Isn't that a pretty strong reason to stay?

151
00:13:26,261 --> 00:13:27,534
- Who is it?
- You...

152
00:13:27,534 --> 00:13:29,381
Don't answer it.

153
00:13:29,381 --> 00:13:31,781
It's not Do Hyun.

154
00:13:31,781 --> 00:13:35,114
You don't need to remember
a con artist's number.

155
00:13:35,114 --> 00:13:36,767
Hello?

156
00:13:38,453 --> 00:13:39,947
Yes.

157
00:13:42,293 --> 00:13:43,811
This spot was originally...

158
00:13:43,811 --> 00:13:47,111
requested by a father who was terminally ill.

159
00:13:47,111 --> 00:13:49,241
His family paid a deposit for months

160
00:13:49,241 --> 00:13:51,314
to reserve it specifically.

161
00:13:52,034 --> 00:13:53,438
There was a mistake on our staff's part.

162
00:13:53,438 --> 00:13:55,811
We sincerely apologize.

163
00:13:55,811 --> 00:13:58,800
How could something like this happen?

164
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,766
I don't understand.

165
00:14:00,766 --> 00:14:03,579
We were quite taken aback
when we found out as well.

166
00:14:03,579 --> 00:14:04,860
"Taken aback?"

167
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:07,380
Do you think this is like canceling
a restaurant reservation?

168
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:09,040
We don't have anything more to say.

169
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,753
That's it?

170
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,773
Once again, we offer our deepest apologies.

171
00:14:14,773 --> 00:14:18,426
You think an apology makes this okay?

172
00:14:20,193 --> 00:14:22,513
So... is there any spot still available?

173
00:14:22,513 --> 00:14:24,279
Yes. Please follow me.

174
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,213
Right here.

175
00:14:42,534 --> 00:14:45,058
Thanks, everyone, for a great day today.

176
00:14:45,058 --> 00:14:47,731
Yeah, thank you.

177
00:14:47,731 --> 00:14:50,536
We will go back to our hotels
and get some rest.

178
00:14:50,536 --> 00:14:52,949
And then we will meet tonight
dressed in our best.

179
00:14:52,949 --> 00:14:54,199
- Okay.
- See you later.

180
00:14:54,199 --> 00:14:55,567
- See you tonight.
- Thank you.

181
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:56,733
Have a good rest.

182
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:59,239
Jun Kyung. How are you?

183
00:15:00,103 --> 00:15:01,563
I'm good.

184
00:15:01,563 --> 00:15:04,170
How are you doing, Dad?

185
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:06,870
Oh, it's nice here.

186
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:09,229
Great weather, a breeze, the ocean.

187
00:15:09,229 --> 00:15:10,776
<i>How about you?</i>

188
00:15:13,925 --> 00:15:16,490
I'm at home with Jun Seo right now.

189
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:17,755
<i>Yeah?</i>

190
00:15:17,755 --> 00:15:19,185
<i>That's really good.</i>

191
00:15:19,185 --> 00:15:21,251
<i>So you're having dinner together then?</i>

192
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:27,463
But Dad...

193
00:15:27,463 --> 00:15:29,096
Yes?

194
00:15:29,096 --> 00:15:30,843
Hold on a second.

195
00:15:36,048 --> 00:15:38,348
- Dad?
- Hi, Jun Seo.

196
00:15:38,348 --> 00:15:40,750
I felt bad leaving without seeing you,

197
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,788
<i>but hearing your voice like this
makes me feel better.</i>

198
00:15:45,337 --> 00:15:47,464
- Dad.
<i>- Yeah?</i>

199
00:15:51,538 --> 00:15:53,344
I'm sorry about what happened before.

200
00:15:54,118 --> 00:15:55,930
Have a good trip.

201
00:16:05,039 --> 00:16:08,473
We don't want to ruin his day. Right?

202
00:16:14,885 --> 00:16:16,804
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

203
00:16:16,804 --> 00:16:19,643
They call just to check in,
even when nothing's wrong.

204
00:16:19,643 --> 00:16:22,176
It's usually parents who worry like that.

205
00:16:22,176 --> 00:16:24,590
Now that they're grown,
they're the ones worrying about me.

206
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:26,850
Sounds like your children turned out well.

207
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:28,596
They did.

208
00:16:28,596 --> 00:16:30,656
My daughter is an OB-GYN,

209
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,756
and my son is in grad school.

210
00:16:32,756 --> 00:16:34,862
They are so nice.

211
00:16:34,862 --> 00:16:36,107
You must be proud.

212
00:16:36,107 --> 00:16:37,916
But it's not that simple.

213
00:16:37,916 --> 00:16:40,175
My son still hasn't found
what he truly loves to do,

214
00:16:40,175 --> 00:16:42,389
and that worries me.

215
00:16:42,389 --> 00:16:44,262
And my daughter hasn't found
someone she loves yet,

216
00:16:44,262 --> 00:16:46,295
that worries me too.

217
00:16:49,430 --> 00:16:51,369
When did we take that picture?

218
00:16:52,689 --> 00:16:55,050
Was it the year you started college?

219
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:57,423
It was my orientation day.

220
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:03,050
A few months before Mom's accident.

221
00:17:04,855 --> 00:17:06,782
It feels so awkward.

222
00:17:07,956 --> 00:17:10,415
Why were we smiling like that?

223
00:18:11,561 --> 00:18:13,301
You...

224
00:18:17,285 --> 00:18:19,309
You look good.

225
00:18:22,769 --> 00:18:24,482
Honey?

226
00:18:27,036 --> 00:18:30,089
You know... thinking back,

227
00:18:30,089 --> 00:18:34,089
our family wasn't that happy
even before Mom's accident.

228
00:18:35,422 --> 00:18:37,935
But we weren't unhappy either.

229
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:43,470
Do you think so?

230
00:18:45,870 --> 00:18:47,483
Right.

231
00:18:47,483 --> 00:18:49,263
We were just... ordinary.

232
00:18:50,763 --> 00:18:52,353
We...

233
00:18:57,683 --> 00:18:59,456
No, I...

234
00:19:01,627 --> 00:19:05,260
I think I blamed Mom for my unhappiness.

235
00:19:06,216 --> 00:19:08,235
It was just my fault.

236
00:19:14,009 --> 00:19:17,230
Geez, the power is out again.

237
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,072
- Hey.
- Yeah?

238
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,610
Do you think this ever happened
when Mom was alone?

239
00:19:47,926 --> 00:19:50,022
<i>She must've been scared.</i>

240
00:19:51,354 --> 00:19:53,593
<i>Yeah.</i>

241
00:19:53,593 --> 00:19:55,566
<i>Probably lonely, too.</i>

242
00:20:04,415 --> 00:20:05,699
Honey.

243
00:20:05,699 --> 00:20:07,912
Why are you sitting in the dark?

244
00:20:13,213 --> 00:20:15,586
Oh, the power is out.

245
00:20:21,475 --> 00:20:23,110
There.

246
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:25,285
It's bright now.

247
00:20:25,285 --> 00:20:28,718
Next time the lights go out, over there...

248
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:35,817
Honey.

249
00:20:38,158 --> 00:20:39,260
I'm sorry.

250
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:41,926
I shouldn't have said that. I'm sorry.

251
00:20:44,182 --> 00:20:46,056
Don't cry.

252
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:50,262
You were scared, weren't you?

253
00:20:51,456 --> 00:20:52,830
I'm so sorry.

254
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:54,550
I'm sorry I came home late.

255
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:56,436
Honey, don't cry.

256
00:21:18,196 --> 00:21:20,975
It wasn't too late.

257
00:21:20,975 --> 00:21:22,760
I always had you

258
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,230
right by my side.

259
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:28,570
That's why I felt sorry every day,

260
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:32,876
and grateful every day.

261
00:21:32,876 --> 00:21:35,916
- Honey.
- Don't cry.

262
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:38,609
Everyone is waiting for you outside.

263
00:21:42,016 --> 00:21:44,056
You...

264
00:21:44,056 --> 00:21:46,309
You look amazing today.

265
00:21:46,309 --> 00:21:47,709
Huh?

266
00:21:48,549 --> 00:21:52,436
That woman, Ja Yeong.

267
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,570
She's pretty.

268
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:56,662
She looks good with you.

269
00:21:57,390 --> 00:22:00,469
Don't say that.

270
00:22:00,469 --> 00:22:04,629
Don't hesitate anymore. Don't hold back.

271
00:22:05,830 --> 00:22:07,470
You should

272
00:22:08,289 --> 00:22:11,163
think about yourself,

273
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,970
and live for yourself.

274
00:22:14,696 --> 00:22:19,636
I want you to be truly happy.

275
00:22:19,636 --> 00:22:21,383
Okay.

276
00:22:21,383 --> 00:22:24,550
Every single day...

277
00:22:24,550 --> 00:22:26,216
be happy.

278
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:31,082
